   =20
      Bored Apes
   =20
 =20
Speaking of =E2=80=A6=C2=A0all that =E2=80=A6 Jessica Klein of Input went t=
o some=C2=A0Bored Ape Yacht Club parties:The yacht event is the big kickoff=
 party for the weeklong Ape Fest 2021, the first time BAYC members have gat=
hered IRL in such large numbers. It=E2=80=99s the highlight of the NFT.NYC =
conference, which features speakers like Reddit co-founder Alexis Ohanian a=
nd entrepreneur Gary Vaynerchuk and draws more than 5,000 non-fungible toke=
n fanatics to the city.The BAYC members eat bananas (seriously) and wear br=
anded sweatshirts to show that they belong. Some are dressed in leather jac=
kets or Hawaiian shirts that match their cartoon apes=E2=80=99 outfits so f=
ellow club members can recognize them IRL. =E2=80=9CYou=E2=80=99re [insert =
Twitter handle]?!=E2=80=9D is an enthusiastic refrain heard throughout the =
week.It is an exciting time to be an ape. Launched in April by four pseudon=
ymous thirtysomethings =E2=80=94 Gargamel, Gordon Goner, Emperor Tomato Ket=
chup, and No Sass =E2=80=94 through their company Yuga Labs, BAYC is a coll=
ection of 10,000 unique digital head-and-shoulders drawings with a variety =
of traits, some quite rare (and thus more valuable). The floor price of a B=
ored Ape =E2=80=94 which initially went on sale for about $250 each =E2=80=
=94 has reached six figures. One rare ape sold at Sotheby=E2=80=99s for mor=
e than $3.4 million last month. ...The apes are for the sneakerheads and mu=
sic fans. The investment is not just in the artwork, but in membership to a=
 club =E2=80=94 one skewing white, male, and young =E2=80=94 that grants ac=
cess to worlds that otherwise might seem unattainable. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99=
s like an adrenaline rush, to be where the culture is going,=E2=80=9D Danie=
l says.I suppose you could just bracket this out of finance. Non-fungible t=
okens are art investing, or streetwear, or a golf-club membership, or somet=
hing other than a financial investment, so you don=E2=80=99t have to consid=
er them as investments for your hedge fund and we never need to talk about =
them again in this financial newsletter. I can=E2=80=99t feel quite confide=
nt that that is the right answer. It would be nice though.
