om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Volcano bonds</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">First of all let=E2=80=99s just apprec=
iate the words here, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlYmxvY2tjcnlwdG8uY29tL2xpbmtlZC8xMjQ5=
NTUvZWwtc2FsdmFkb3ItZ292ZXJubWVudC1zdHJpa2VzLWRlYWwtd2l0aC1iaXRmaW5leC1ibG9=
ja3N0cmVhbS10by1pc3N1ZS0xLWJpbGxpb24tYml0Y29pbi1ib25k/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBf2dcecee" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">these are good words</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">El Salvador has struck a deal with crypto firms Blockstrea=
m and iFinex to advance its efforts in the bitcoin market.=C2=A0</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The country is set to issue so-called Bitcoin bonds t=
o "accelerate hyperbitcoinization and bring about a new financial system on=
 top of Bitcoin," according to Blockstream.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">El Salvador could issue $1 billion worth of bitcoin bonds via Blocks=
tream's Liquid Network. The proceeds of the bond issuance could support the=
 development of volcano-powered bitcoin mining.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">"This bond offering is something we think will be attractive to =
a wide range of investors ranging from cryptocurrency investors, investors =
seeking yield, HODLers, and ordinary people," Blockstream said in a blog po=
st.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hyperbitcoinization, volca=
no-powered Bitcoin mining, HODLers, it is the good stuff. People are appare=
ntly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.2806=
54/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYml0ZmluZXguY29tL3Bvc3RzLzc0MQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
adbf3ca7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">calling this</a> a=C2=A0=E2=80=9CVolcano Bond=E2=80=9D an=
d who am I to resist. Volcano Bond.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Second =
let=E2=80=99s take a look at the termsheet, which as far as I can tell <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cH=
M6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9icmFkbWlsbHNjYW4vc3RhdHVzLzE0NjI0ODU3MzA5NjIzMjU1MDg/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe5df82aa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">consists</a> of tweeted <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6L=
y90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9qdmljdG9ybWVuZGVzcy9zdGF0dXMvMTQ2MjI2NTIzNDUzMDQ3NjAzMg/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB96684acd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">photos</a> of a young bearded man=
 in a backwards white baseball cap who is also the president of El Salvador=
, standing in front of a PowerPoint slide=C2=A0while a roomful of=C2=A0cryp=
to fans take pictures. That Powerpoint slide is the termsheet? I will summa=
rize it briefly. (Coindesk summarizes it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL2J1=
c2luZXNzLzIwMjEvMTEvMjEvZWwtc2FsdmFkb3ItdG8tY3JlYXRlLWJpdGNvaW4tY2l0eS11c2U=
tNTAwbS1vZi1wbGFubmVkLTFiLWJvbmQtb2ZmZXJpbmctdG8tYnV5LW1vcmUtY3J5cHRvLw/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc446ea7d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">here</a>, noting that=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9CPresident Nayib Bukele told a raucous crowd=E2=80=9D about the bonds, an=
d the associated =E2=80=9CBitcoin City,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cin a Saturday nig=
ht presentation at Bitcoin Week in El Salvador.=E2=80=9D) The Volcano Bonds=
 are a $1 billion bond, denominated in U.S. dollars, with a 10-year maturit=
y in, apparently, January 2032. They pay 6.5% annual interest. El Salvador =
will invest half of the proceeds in =E2=80=9Cinfrastructure build,=E2=80=9D=
 and put the rest into Bitcoin. It will hold those Bitcoins for five years,=
 and then sell them over the remaining five years. If it makes money on tho=
se sales, then =E2=80=9C50% of Bitcoin investment proceeds returned to inve=
stors once initial $500M Bitcoin investment is recovered.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=9CBlockstream models show at the end of the 10th year of the bond, the ann=
ual percentage yield will be 146% due to Bitcoin=E2=80=99s projected apprec=
iation, [Blockstream Chief Strategy Officer Samson] Mow said, forecasting B=
itcoin will hit the $1 million mark within five years,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMjEvZWwtc2FsdmFkb3ItcGxh=
bnMtMWItaW4tdG9rZW5pemVkLWJpdGNvaW4tYm9uZHMtYnVrZWxlLXNheXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTE=
yMjIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdX=
RtX3Rlcm09MjExMTIyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
Bf770617d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">sure</a>. You can buy it in units as small as $100, and =
you can pay in dollars, Tether or Bitcoin.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Third, let=E2=80=99s ask, is this a good investment? I don=E2=80=99t know; =
it depends on whether (1) El Salvador pays you back and (2) Bitcoin goes up=
 over the next 10 years. Helpfully there are=C2=A0other investments that de=
pend on the same factors. For instance, you can just buy Bitcoin. Or=C2=A0E=
l Salvador has other international bonds; you can buy them. One of them is =
a $500 million U.S. dollar bond issued in 2002 and maturing in April 2032, =
around the same time as the Volcano Bonds.[1] It has a coupon of 8.25% per =
year. It <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.=
280654/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm91cnNlLmx1L3NlY3VyaXR5L1hTMDE0NjE3MzM3MS81NjY1Mw/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB35cc72bd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">is listed</a>=C2=A0on the Luxembo=
urg Stock Exchange and seems to trade at about 73 or 74 cents on the dollar=
. Call it the Non-Volcano Bond, for convenience.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">If you had $100,000, you could buy $100,000 of the new Volcano Bond. =
Or you could do this trade:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; paddi=
ng-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Spend =
about $75,000 to buy $100,000 face amount of the Non-Volcano Bond; then</li=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Spend $25,000 to buy $25,000 worth of=
 Bitcoin.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m using round num=
bers here; the Non-Volcano Bond would actually cost you less than $75,000 a=
t prices on my screen, though I=E2=80=99m not sure you could really get it =
at that price.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, the Volcano Bond pays y=
ou 6.5% interest, so you get $6,500 a year for 10 years. The Non-Volcano Bo=
nd pays 8.25% interest, so $8,250 a year for 10 years. So, advantage Non-Vo=
lcano.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At maturity, in 2032, the Non-Volcan=
o Bond pays off $100,000, and the Volcano Bond pays off $100,000. (Or they =
both default, I mean; they are instruments of the same government and seem =
to have the same seniority and mature at almost the same time.[2]) So this =
one is a draw.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Volcano Bond inves=
ts a portion of your money in Bitcoin, locks it up for five years,=C2=A0and=
 then=C2=A0liquidates the Bitcoin over the next five years and gives you ha=
lf the appreciation. But you could do the same thing with the Bitcoin that =
you bought in the Non-Volcano Package. Let=E2=80=99s say for simplicity tha=
t Bitcoin doubles. Then El Salvador will have $1 billion of Bitcoin proceed=
s, or $500 million of appreciation; Volcano Bond holders will get half of t=
hat, or $250 million. Your share, with $100,000 of Volcano Bonds, comes to =
$25,000, on top of the principal and interest that you get back.=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile in the Non-Volcano Package you bought=
 $25,000 worth of Bitcoin. So when Bitcoin doubles you have $50,000 of Bitc=
oin, on top of the principal and interest that you got back from the bonds.=
 So, advantage Non-Volcano. Non-Volcano also wins for other Bitcoin growth,=
 or decline, scenarios. If Bitcoin goes to $1 million, your $100,000 Volcan=
o Bond will be worth about $491,700;=C2=A0your Non-Volcano Package will be =
worth about $516,700.[3]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Non-Volcano Pa=
ckage is a way to invest in Bitcoin plus the credit of El Salvador that is=
=C2=A0<em>strictly better in every scenario than investing in the Volcano B=
onds</em>. Oh no wait sorry; from <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9icmFkbWlsbHNjYW4=
vc3RhdHVzLzE0NjI0ODU3MzA5NjIzMjU1MDgvcGhvdG8vMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB12=
5d6288" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">the termsheet</a>, here you go:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Citizenship by investment qualification: Investments &gt;=
=3D $100,000 will qualify investors for citizenship-by-investment applicati=
ons after a five year term.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
at=E2=80=99s only for the Volcano Bond. So if you are looking to buy El Sal=
vador citizenship the Volcano Bond does have that advantage over the Non-Vo=
lcano Package.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point I want to make her=
e is that this is an example of market segmentation by standing in front of=
 a PowerPoint presentation at a Bitcoin party wearing a backwards baseball =
cap. This is market segmentation by slapping a cool name =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=
=80=9CVolcano Bond=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0on a bond that is=C2=A0<em>stric=
tly worse than a readily available alternative</em>. This is market segment=
ation by combining a normal thing with (1) crypto and (2) a huge markup, an=
d then marketing it to crypto people who want to pay the huge markup not to=
 buy crypto (they can just buy crypto!) but to=C2=A0<em>buy into a crypto a=
dventure</em>.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I understand that I am being=
 dense by writing all of this. The point of the Volcano Bonds is that they =
live on a crypto trading platform and people who like crypto will buy them =
and trade them with each other and feel a sense of kinship and community an=
d fun. They are HODLers and whales, they get to hang out with the president=
 of a country on a Saturday night, all this stuff. The specific terms of th=
e financial investment don=E2=80=99t matter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Fine! Yes! Fine! People like to join clubs! People like to buy things for=
 reasons other than their financial returns! It is weird to do this with a =
financial instrument! I feel like this is the main story of finance in 2021=
! =E2=80=9CI bought that stock [bond, cryptocurrency, etc.] to be part of a=
 cool club, not because it made financial sense=E2=80=9D! I don=E2=80=99t k=
now!</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpa=
dding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
