 solid; background-color: #ccc;">a good little statistic</a>:</p><blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JPMorgan=E2=80=99s investment bankers haven=
=E2=80=99t worked on any Tesla offering or transaction since 2016, accordin=
g to public records. When JPMorgan worked on Tesla=E2=80=99s 2010 initial p=
ublic offering of stock and several capital-markets transactions in the fol=
lowing years, it was usually ranked behind rivals such as Goldman Sachs Gro=
up Inc. and Morgan Stanley.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JPMorgan has be=
en paid about $15 million by Tesla for advice and capital-markets work in t=
he past decade, while Goldman has made about $90 million, according to Deal=
ogic.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That number is not compr=
ehensive; that=E2=80=99s not all the money that JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. ha=
s made from Tesla Inc. That=E2=80=99s just fees. For instance, as we <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25793453.280654/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMTYvanBtb3JnYW4=
